Hi lukeschlather, thanks for the report!
</p>
<p>
You should be able to do this already through the <code>http_request_args</code> filter:
</p>
<pre class="wiki">add_filter( 'http_request_args', function ( $args ) {
	$args['sslcertificates'] = '/path/to/certs.crt';
	return $args;
} );
</pre><p>
There's not really a way to tell if the user passed their own in, but checking if it's <code>=== ABSPATH . WPINC . '/certificates/ca-bundle.crt'</code> is pretty safe.
</p>
